{
  "stem": "2522.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so, in the fall of 1945, I went back to-- to Trencin.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By that time, my sister had returned from concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sold some of the properties that my father had, because I didn't care about property.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Took money and went to Prague for two years, studying English, French, Spanish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Going to theater every night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Going to-- going to concert every afternoon.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You know, sort of filling-- filling myself up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In December of 1947, I-- I got actually a teacher's certificate from the University, in English, so I could teach English.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "By that time, I was absolutely convinced that-- that there's no place for me in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Especially after seeing the criminal element from the underground rise to the top in Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Much of the so-called partisan movement was criminal, and they are the ones who took some of the key positions.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In fact, the man with whom I shared fleas and lice in some of the hay rakes that we slept together, Staudinger, became the chief prosecuting judge in show trials, including the hanging of the former president of Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in my opinion, he was just a criminal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So by that time, Mr.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Kubicek, who had left Slovakia in 1939 for Basel and left his wife and his child in the care of my father, offered to take me to America.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Which, of course, was what everybody wanted to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Couldn't get me a visa, an immigration visa.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- but it was quite becoming apparent the Communists would be taking over.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so, five days before the Communists took over in February of 1948, I just walked out of Czechoslovakia on a train with a short term visa for England under the pretense that I'm going to school.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Electronic school, to study electronic engineering in England.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
